rComments: Prof Magnusson is a kind professor however kind of hard to follow. Majority of her lectures strayed far away from the texts and deep into irrelevant history. She was entertaining to listen to, and very reasonable. Everything was graded fairly and feedback was always provided. Overall pretty decent prof.

Lots of reading, though fairly spaced out. Although a bit scatter-brained, she's caring and seems very willing to accommodate. Her teaching style might be a bit hard to follow if you're used to taking notes from a powerpoint
Very nice prof, the assignments are fairly interesting. Unfortunately lecture slides aren't very detailed.

Well-known  Shakespeare scholar, publishes a lot. However, as a teacher she is scattered, and had  bad listening skills. At times responded to ?s in a way that showed she forgets she is in a position of power (I have so many things to take care of, it's very hard for me etc). Interrupts students often. Difficult to deal with. Poor management skills
